[{:db/id -1, :genre/id :platformer, :genre/status :implemented, :genre/core-loop ["a sequence of fixed \"platform\" tagged entities the player must reach\n   IN ORDER along a single traversal axis, tracked via a defatom\n   sequence-index (closest analogue to jump-across-gaps progression\n   available without real physics)"], :genre/controls "{:buttons 1, :scheme [\"movement only\"]}", :genre/kami-engine "{:proven-vocab-used [:defatom :set-atom! :nearest-tagged :get-x :get-y], :known-constraints [\"NO jump/gravity primitive exists anywhere in the proven vocabulary or\\n    any reference game -- this is an honest limitation, not an oversight.\\n    This base is a sequential-waypoint traversal, not a true jump-physics\\n    platformer. Real platforming would need a Rust-side physics/collision\\n    system this repo does not have access to from kami-clj logic.\"]}", :genre/note "Deepened beyond the kami-clj-subset logic.clj above: games/platformer/{src,test}\n  now also has a decoupled, pure .cljc action-systems layer -- room-lock camera\n  (kami-genre-base-systems.platformer.camera), whip/sub-weapon/item-crash attack\n  state machines (.weapon), a combo/style-meter rank system (.style), and a\n  boss phase/attack-pattern framework (.boss) -- for a Castlevania-style host\n  (network-isekai / kotoba.kami-host), plus a stairs.cljc extension-point\n  contract so a host can plug in physics-2d's stair/diagonal-movement work\n  without this repo depending on physics-2d directly. This layer targets a\n  different runtime (portable ClojureScript/Clojure, not kami-engine-clj's\n  proven-vocabulary subset) and is verified by its own `clojure -M:test`\n  (games/platformer/deps.edn), NOT by scripts/verify's kami-engine-clj-\n  compile + kami-host-execute WASM pipeline that the other :implemented\n  genres go through -- the two verification paths are not equivalent.", :games/dir "games/platformer"}]